To Install redis server in ubuntu use follow command
====================================================
Link - https://redis.io/download

1- Create a folder with name Redis at any location in your system
2- Go to Redis folder and execute below commands

        wget http://download.redis.io/releases/redis-5.0.7.tar.gz
        tar xzf redis-5.0.7.tar.gz
        cd redis-5.0.7
        make
        make install ( We run this command so we can run redis-server from anywhere we don't need to go src folder every time)
        
 3- To run redis server go to src folder and run redis-server command
 4- To run redis client go to src folder and run redis-cli command
        
        
        
